{"lemma":"بِشْرُ","slug":"بِشْرُ","root":"ب.ش.ر","root_slug":"ب-ش-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ش-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بِشْرُ","root":"بشر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":13},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2588","n2594","n2595","n2596"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%90%D8%B4%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"human"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"humans, humankind","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"skin, outer skin, epidermis","tags":["collective"],"examples":[{"text":"سَأُصْلِيهِ سَقَرَ / وَمَا أَدْرَاكَ مَا سَقَرُ / لَا تُبْقِي وَلَا تَذَرُ / لَوَّاحَةٌ لِلْبَشَرِ / عَلَيْهَا تِسْعَةَ عَشَرَ","english":"I shall cast thee into the hellfire. And what shall acquaint you with what the hellfire be? Neither does it preserve nor does it spare. Scorching the skins. Over it are nineteen [angels guarding]."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to peel, to pare"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shave so as to render the skin visible"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to eat the ground bare"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to take (a matter) into one's own hands"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَشَرَ (bašara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to rejoice at, to become glad, to congratulate, to rejoice"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَشِرَ (bašira) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَشَرَ (bašara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bring good news (to)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to evangelize, to preach the gospel (to)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-West Semitic *baśar- (“flesh, human body”). The original meaning \"flesh\" was replaced by لَحْم (laḥm).\n\nRelated to بَشَر (bašar, “skin”) as rejoicement manifests itself as a complexion of the skin.\n\nCausative of بَشِرَ (bašira, “to rejoice at”). Religious sense is a literal translation of Ancient Greek εὐαγγελίζω (euangelízō), from εὐαγγέλιον (euangélion, “good news, gospel”). Cognate with Hebrew בִּשֵׂר (bisér, biśśēr, “to bring good news”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2588","headword_ar":"بَشَرَ","root":"b$r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$orN","text_ar":"بَشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ab$r","text_ar":"ابشر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibo$aArN","text_ar":"اـِبْشَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pared"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K) a hide, (S, A, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"removing its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$arap","text_ar":"بَشَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"face,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surface,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the skin upon which the hair grew:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"removing its inner part with a large knife:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to Ibn-Buzurj, some of the Arabs say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$arotu AlA^adiyma","text_ar":"بَشَرْتُ الاَدِيمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I removed from the hide its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$arap","text_ar":"بَشَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abo$arotuhu","text_ar":"اَبْشَرْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I exposed to view its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$arap","text_ar":"بَشَرَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that was next to the flesh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=damotuhu","text_ar":"ا=دَمْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"I exposed to view its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adamap","text_ar":"اَدَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"upon which the hair grew. (TA.) [But see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adamapN","text_ar":"اَدَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  Hence the saying in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano A^aHab~a AlquroA=na qaloyabo$uro","text_ar":"مَنْ اَحَبَّ القُرْا=نَ قَلْيَبْشُرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to him who recites it thus, with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$","text_ar":"ش"},{"kind":"text","text":"; meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whoso loveth the Kur-án, let him make himself light of flesh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by not eating more than will be sufficient,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so prepare himself] for [reading, or reciting,] it, [like as one prepares a horse for running,] because eating much causes one to forget it. (TA.) ―         -b3-  Hence also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$ara AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"بَشَرَ الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n. as above, (S, K,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a swarm of locusts)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stripped the ground;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ate what was upon the ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon its surface;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though the exterior of the ground were its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$arap","text_ar":"بَشَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$ara","text_ar":"بَشَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n. as above, (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He clipped"},{"kind":"text","text":"his mustache"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much, so that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$arap","text_ar":"بَشَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exterior of the skin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became apparent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) This the Muslim is commanded to do. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$araniY fulaAnN biwajohK HasanK","text_ar":"بَشَرَنِى فُلَانٌ بِوَجْهٍ حَسَنٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one met me with a cheerful countenance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) See also 2, in two places. ―         -b6-  And see 3.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$ira","text_ar":"بَشِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAar, S, Msb, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$ara","text_ar":"بَشَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$orN","text_ar":"بَشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bu$uwrN","text_ar":"بُشُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ab$r","text_ar":"ابشر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which is the most common, though extr. in respect of analogy, as being quasi-pass. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$ara","text_ar":"بَشَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHjm","text_ar":"احجم"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHnj","text_ar":"احنج"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AErD","text_ar":"اعرض"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aq$E","text_ar":"اقشع"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Akb~","text_ar":"اكبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anhj","text_ar":"انهج"},{"kind":"text","text":", (mentioned by MF in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hnj","text_ar":"حنج"},{"kind":"text","text":"as the only other instances of the kind,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Axlj","text_ar":"اخلج"},{"kind":"text","text":", (added in the TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xlj","text_ar":"خلج"},{"kind":"text","text":",)] (S, A, Mgh, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibo$aArN","text_ar":"اـِبْشَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astb$r","text_ar":"استبشر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tb$~r","text_ar":"تبشّر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A;) [originally,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became changed in his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$arap","text_ar":"بَشَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"complexion"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the annunciation of an event:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$~arahu","text_ar":"بَشَّرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he rejoiced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became rejoiced;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, A, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bika*aA","text_ar":"بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by, such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by, the annunciation of such a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IAar, S, K. *) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ataAniY A^amorN ba$irotu bihi","text_ar":"اَتَانِى اَمْرٌ بَشِرْتُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An affair happened to me whereat I rejoiced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whereby I became rejoiced."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bimawoluwdK","text_ar":"بِمَوْلُودٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abo$ara","text_ar":"اَبْشَرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rejoiced"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the annunciation of a new-born child"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bixayorK","text_ar":"بِخَيْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abo$iro","text_ar":"اَبْشِرْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rejoice thou"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the annunciation of a good event"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K.) And in the same sense ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abo$iruwA","text_ar":"اَبْشِرُوا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in the Kur xli. 30. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","A","K","TA","IAar","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n2594","headword_ar":"بُشْرٌ","root":"b$r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bu$oraY","text_ar":"بُشْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  It is also a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bu$urN","text_ar":"بُشُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$uwrN","text_ar":"بَشُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$iyrN","text_ar":"بَشِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n$r","text_ar":"نشر"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["TA"]},{"entry_id":"n2595","headword_ar":"بِشْرٌ","root":"b$r","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cheerfulness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"openness and pleasantness,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":208},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of countenance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K, * TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"happiness, joy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gladness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 192.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa Hasanu Albi$ori","text_ar":"هُوَ حَسَنُ البِشْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is cheerful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"open and pleasant, in countenance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n2596","headword_ar":"بَشَرٌ","root":"b$r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$arapN","text_ar":"بَشَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alba$aru","text_ar":"البَشَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mankind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the human being:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K:) applied to the male and to the female; and used alike as sing. and pl. (Msb, K, TA) and dual: (TA:) so that you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa ba$arN","text_ar":"هُوَ بَشَرٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is a human being,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiYa ba$arN","text_ar":"هِىَ بَشَرٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She is a human being,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo ba$arN","text_ar":"هُمْ بَشَرٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They"},{"kind":"text","text":"(more than two)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are human beings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humaA ba$arN","text_ar":"هُمَا بَشَرٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They two are human beings:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) but sometimes it has the dual form; (Msb, K;) as in the Kur xxiii. 49; (Msb, TA;) though the Arabs may have used the dual form in the sense of the sing.: (MF:) and sometimes it has a pl., namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abo$aArN","text_ar":"اَبْشَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) This is a secondary application of the word: (Msb:) i. e., this signification is tropical; or, as some say, the word is so much used in this sense as to be, so used, conventionally regarded as proper; the sense not depending upon its having another word connected with it: but in the S and K, and by the generality of authors, this signification is given as proper. (MF.) Some say that a human being is thus called because his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$arap","text_ar":"بَشَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is bare of hair and of wool. (MF.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw Alba$ari","text_ar":"اَبُو البَشَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The father of mankind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Adam."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","MF"]}]}}